{"body":"<a href="#"><img alt="P1" src="https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=7" align="top"></a> **"Select All" ignores active search filter**

When a search filter is active, clicking "Select All" iterates over the full unfiltered `models` array (line 688), silently adding hidden/non-matching models to `selectedIds`. The rendered cards only show the filtered subset, but the status counter will report all models as selected (e.g. "20 models selected" while only 3 cards are visible). The `updateSelectAllLabel()` check on line 685 also compares `selectedIds.size === models.length` against the full set, so the toggle label is misleading when a filter is active.

Fix by scoping the toggle to only the currently visible models:

```suggestion
	selectAllBtn.addEventListener("click", () => {
		var currentFilter = searchInp?.value.trim() || null;
		var q = currentFilter ? currentFilter.toLowerCase() : null;
		var visibleModels = q
			? models.filter((mdl) => mdl.displayName.toLowerCase().includes(q) || mdl.id.toLowerCase().includes(q))
			: models;
		var allVisible = visibleModels.every((mdl) => selectedIds.has(mdl.id));
		if (allVisible) {
			for (var mdl of visibleModels) selectedIds.delete(mdl.id);
		} else {
			for (var mdl of visibleModels) selectedIds.add(mdl.id);
		}
		updateSelectAllLabel();
		updateStatus();
		renderCards(currentFilter);
	});
